<TITLE> HC extends Tarique's bail by four months </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 6 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Monday extended the bail of Tarique Rahman, son of former prime minister Khaleda Zia, and 74 others by four months in separate cases. The vacation bench of justices AKM Fazlur Rahman and Sheikh Abdul Awal ordered the extension on appeals. Chamber judge Joynul Abedin of the Appellate Division upheld the bails of ex-minister Mirza Abbas, ex-state minister Mohiuddin Khan Alamgir, former lawmaker Mosaddak Ali Falu, Jubo League leader Mirza Azam, controversial businessman Giasuddin Al Mamun, ward commissioner Abdul Quaiyum and businessman Giridhari Lal Modi. Abbas had got bail from the High Court in cases relating to amassing illegal wealth, and allotment of government houses and plots. Alamgir secured bail in a graft case relating to setting up a printing press, and Mosaddak Ali Falu was granted bail in the relief materials misappropriation case. The Appellate Division upheld the High Court bail to Mamun in four extortion cases. bd
